<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1" ?><grammar><bgcolour>FFFFFF</bgcolour><darkcolour>A6416E</darkcolour><section><title>Past Simple</title><sectiontitle>Use the Past Simple to talk about finished actions in the past.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Pre-intGRAM_2_1_1.mp3</titlesound><text1></text1><sound1>Pre-intGRAM_2_1_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>Mozart &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;lived&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; in Austria.</text1a><text2></text2><sound2>Pre-intGRAM_2_1_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;went&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; to China in 1997.</text2a><titlesound2>Pre-intGRAM_2_1_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>To make the Past Simple negative use &lt;I&gt;didn't&lt;/I&gt; + verb.</sectiontitle2><text3>I went to the party.</text3><sound3>Pre-intGRAM_2_1_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;didn't go&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; to the party.</text3a><text4>She visited us.</text4><sound4>Pre-intGRAM_2_1_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>She &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;didn't visit&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; us.</text4a></section><section><title>Past Simple</title><sectiontitle>To make questions in the Past Simple use (Question word +) &lt;I&gt;did&lt;/I&gt; + subject + verb.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Pre-intGRAM_2_1_7.mp3</titlesound><text1>I stayed in England.</text1><sound1>Pre-intGRAM_2_1_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Did you stay&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; in England?</text1a><text2>I worked in London.</text2><sound2>Pre-intGRAM_2_1_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Where did&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; you work?</text2a><titlesound2>Pre-intGRAM_2_1_10.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>To make short answers, use &lt;I&gt;did&lt;/I&gt; or &lt;I&gt;didn't&lt;/I&gt;.</sectiontitle2><text3>A: Did you go to the party? B: Yes, I went to the party.  </text3><sound3>Pre-intGRAM_2_1_11.mp3</sound3><text3a>A: Did you go to the party? B: Yes, I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;did.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text3a><text4>A: Did you see John? B: No, I didn't see John. </text4><sound4>Pre-intGRAM_2_1_12.mp3</sound4><text4a>A: Did you see John? B: No, I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;didn't.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text4a></section></grammar>